    "recap_headline": "East Carolina University",
    "recap_text": "GREENVILLE, N.C.\u00a0\u2013\nEast Carolina (13-8-1) held off a late push from Elon (9-11) to secure a 4-3 midweek victory Tuesday evening at Clark-LeClair Stadium. The Pirates built an early lead behind timely hitting and a strong start on the mound before weathering a three-run eighth inning from the Phoenix to seal the win.\nEast Carolina threatened early in the first inning when\nAustin Irby\nwas hit by a pitch and\nCarlos Jacome\nfollowed with a double down the right field line to place two runners in scoring position. However, Elon escaped the jam to keep the game scoreless.\nThe Pirates broke through in the second inning with two-out production.\nDavin Whitaker\nsparked the rally with a double, and\nWalker Barron\ndelivered with a clutch RBI double to left center to open the scoring.\nBraden Burress\nfollowed with a single to left field, plating Barron and extending the lead to 2-0.\nECU added to its advantage in the fourth inning as\nColby Wallace\nlaunched his first home run of the season, a 362-foot shot to left field, pushing the Pirates ahead 3-0.\nThe offense struck again in the sixth. Whitaker reached with a single and later scored after Wallace and Barron each recorded base hits, with Barron driving in his second run of the night to give ECU a 4-0 cushion.\nOn the mound,\nRyan Towers\ndelivered his strongest outing in a Pirate uniform, earning the win after tossing 5.0 scoreless innings. The right-hander allowed just three hits while striking out five, marking season highs in both innings pitched and strikeouts. Towers kept Elon off balance throughout his outing, inducing consistent weak contact.\nElon mounted its lone offensive surge in the eighth inning, stringing together four hits to score three runs and cut the deficit to 4-3. The Phoenix capitalized on a triple and consecutive RBI hits to apply pressure late, but ECU turned to\nSean Jenkins\nto halt the rally. Jenkins entered the inning and limited further damage before returning in the ninth to close the door.\nJenkins recorded his second save of the season, tossing 1.2 scoreless innings with two strikeouts to secure the victory.\nOffensively, the Pirates were led by Wallace and Barron. Wallace went 2-for-3 with a home run and an RBI, while Barron also finished 2-for-3 with a game-high two RBIs. Whitaker added a 2-for-4 performance with two runs scored, and Jacome contributed two doubles as part of ECU's nine-hit effort. Burress chipped in with an RBI single in the second to help fuel the early momentum.\nDefensively, the Pirates turned key double plays and limited Elon to 3-for-11 hitting with runners in scoring position, helping preserve the narrow victory.\nEast Carolina improves to 13-8-1 on the season and continues to build momentum heading into conference play, while Elon falls to 9-11.\nThe Pirates look ahead to conference play, starting on Friday, March 20, when they host UAB to kick off the conference and the race for first place."
  },
